CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 24, 1959, pg. 3 reads: "Firebug's Work - The home where the Dupree children died (right) is in the tinderbox area in the "bottoms" of Braddock where three fires within one week have led police and firemen to suspect arson."
TitMainTitle: Two framed buildings destroyed by fire, with destroyed brick building on left, 1228 Washington Street, Braddock
